name: Jim Harbaugh
summary: During the Chargers vs. Broncos game, head coach Jim Harbaugh abruptly left the sideline due to an undisclosed illness. Reports indicate that Harbaugh experienced an arrhythmia, a heart rhythm irregularity. He briefly visited the medical tent before returning to coach the team. Harbaugh's absence raised concerns, with his status initially listed as questionable to return. name: Dennis Quaid
summary: Dennis Quaid, well-known for his acting roles portraying U.S. presidents, has recently voiced his support for former President Donald Trump. Quaid made an appearance at a Trump rally in Coachella, California, where he expressed his admiration for Trump, calling him his "favorite president of the 21st century." Quaid's speech urged attendees to choose between support for TikTok, a popular social media platform, and allegiance to the U.S. Constitution. Quaid's endorsement of Trump has sparked various reactions, with some critiquing his political stance. Despite facing opposition, Quaid maintains his support for Trump, reiterating the need to make a choice between the two sides.

name: Trump assassination attempt
summary: The Sheriff of Riverside County, California, has reported that an armed man named Vem Miller was apprehended near a Trump rally in Coachella. Miller was allegedly carrying multiple weapons at the time of his arrest, and the Sheriff believes that deputies may have prevented a potential assassination attempt on Trump. However, federal officials have stated that there is no evidence to support an assassination attempt. Despite this, some members of the public believe that this incident, along with two previous attempted assassinations, are part of a conspiracy. According to a Newsweek poll, one in three Americans believe that the assassination attempts on Trump are a hoax.
